22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Felon-musk-criticised-at-video-game-competition-bring-back-twitter-4341582%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Felon-musk-criticised-at-video-game-competition-bring-back-twitter-4341582%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20Needs%20to%20Move%20From%20Mouthing%20Platitudes%20for%20Peace%20to%20Helping%20Russia%20and%20Ukraine%20Broker%20Peace%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28161248%2FFJIXugOXoAMKMh-.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Vladimir%20Putin%20of%20Russia%20attacked%20Ukraine%20in%20February%202022%20ostensibly%20to%20discourage%20it%20from%20joining%20NATO.%20Another%20possible%20aim%2C%20which%20came%20into%20play%20later%2C%20was%20to%20annex%20the%20Russian-speaking%20areas%2C%20whose%20population%20had%20complained%20of%20being%20discriminated%20against.%20If%20these%20were%20indeed%20the%20aims%2C%20then%20in%20military%20terms%20these%20had%20not%20been%20thought%20through%20properly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20war%2C%20Russian%20and%20Belarusian%20forces%20carried%20out%20joint%20exercises%20in%20the%20guise%20of%20which%20the%20concentration%20of%20force%20was%20achieved.%20The%20Russians%20started%20with%20massive%20armour%20thrusts%20on%20more%20than%20one%20axis%2C%20most%20importantly%20to%20take%20Kyiv%2C%20the%20capital%20of%20Ukraine.%20At%20the%20start%20of%20the%20invasion%2C%20some%20analysts%20were%20of%20the%20opinion%20that%20Kyiv%20would%20fall%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20a%20few%20days%20whereas%20others%20were%20of%20the%20opinion%20that%20it%20was%20not%20possible%20within%20a%20short%20timeframe%20and%20that%20this%20goal%20could%20take%20many%20months.%20It%20appears%20that%20the%20Russian%20generalship%20had%20studied%20Clausewitz%20and%20aimed%20for%20the%20capital%20in%20the%20hope%20that%20once%20the%20capital%20fell%20the%20whole%20nation%20would%20crumble%20and%20surrender.%20Analysts%20who%20assumed%20Kyiv%20would%20eventually%20fall%20assumed%20that%20Moscow%20would%20establish%20a%20puppet%20government%20which%20would%20act%20as%20a%20buffer%20between%20NATO%20and%20Russia.%20That%20would%20also%20ensure%20that%20not%20only%20were%20Russian-speaking%20areas%20effectively%20annexed%2C%20but%20also%20that%20Russian%20domination%20of%20the%20Black%20Sea%20would%20be%20total%20and%20obviate%20NATO%20and%20others%20from%20using%20it%20for%20military%20or%20trade%20purposes%2C%20including%20the%20export%20of%20Ukraine%20wheat%20and%20grains%20to%20Europe%20and%20other%20places.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20timeframe%20was%20unrealistic%2C%20given%20the%20specific%20application%20of%20forces%20as%20well%20as%20the%20timing%2C%20when%20there%20was%20still%20snow%20and%20the%20temperature%20was%20around%20minus%2020%20degrees%20Celsius.%20Russian%20tanks%20found%20it%20difficult%20to%20move%20across%20the%20country%20for%20these%20reasons.%20The%20armour%20thrust%20on%20roads%20could%20be%20easily%20stopped%20by%20small%20groups%20of%20infantry%20commandos%20by%20knocking%20off%20a%20few%20tanks%20near%20bottlenecks%20or%20destroying%20bridges%2C%20which%20would%20make%20it%20impossible%20for%20the%20follow%20up%20tanks%20and%20more%20importantly%20the%20logistic%20elements%20which%20carry%20fuel%20for%20the%20tanks%2C%20ammunition%2C%20food%20and%20tents%20for%20the%20force%20which%20also%20included%20fuel%20for%20keeping%20them%20warm%20to%20save%20them%20from%20snow%20and%20extreme%20cold%20weather.%20The%20Russians%20had%20failed%20to%20consider%20the%20ground%20realities%20in%20detail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20it%20happened%2C%20the%20Russian%20advancing%20columns%20were%20struck%20on%20all%20the%20axes%2C%20which%20was%20the%20first%20indicator%20of%20a%20major%20defeat%20in%20the%20ongoing%20operations.%20The%20troops%20in%20the%20tanks%20and%20open%20trucks%20had%20to%20bear%20the%20extreme%20cold%20without%20sufficient%20food%20or%20shelter%2C%20which%20is%20a%20great%20demoralising%20factor%20in%20war.%20It%20appears%20that%20the%20Russian%20general%20staff%20did%20not%20remember%20lessons%20from%20the%20Second%20World%20War%2C%20where%20the%20Nazi%20German%20attacks%20on%20Russia%20were%20defeated%20by%20%E2%80%9CGeneral%20Frost%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9CGeneral%20Mud%E2%80%9D%20(weather%20conditions).%20The%20next%20important%20point%20was%20that%20before%20the%20Russian%20infantry%20started%20clearing%20Kyiv%2C%20which%20is%20a%20very%20large%20objective%2C%20it%20had%20to%20be%20isolated%20by%20tanks%20and%20infantry%20picquets%20out%20in%20the%20open%20to%20ensure%20that%20no%20reinforcements%20or%20logistics%20got%20into%20Kyiv%20from%20outside.%20This%20was%20not%20possible%20in%20the%20sub-zero%20temperature%20as%20the%20picqueting%20troops%20had%20to%20be%20supplied%20food%2C%20clothing%20and%20some%20cover%20and%20fuel%20to%20keep%20them%20warm%2C%20which%20was%20a%20Herculean%20task.%20Even%20if%20they%20were%20to%20isolate%20only%20a%20small%20portion%20of%20Kyiv%2C%20it%20was%20still%20unthinkable%20as%20major%20reinforcements%20from%20the%20rest%20of%20Kyiv%20would%20not%20allow%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Drones%20Fighting%20Drones%20in%20Ukraine%20Heralds%20a%20New%20Era%20of%20Warfare%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fdrones-fighting-drones-in-ukraine-heralds-a-new-era-of-warfare%5C%22%3EDrones%20Fighting%20Drones%20in%20Ukraine%20Heralds%20a%20New%20Era%20of%20Warfare%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETanks%20are%20virtually%20ineffective%20inside%20a%20built-up%20area%20as%20their%20guns%20can%20fire%20only%2015%20degrees%20of%20elevation%2C%20and%20with%20high%20rise%20buildings%20on%20all%20sides%20even%20a%20small%20infantry%20section%20and%20a%20few%20snipers%20would%20not%20let%20the%20attacking%20forces%20dominate.%20I%20personally%20had%20some%20good%20experience%20of%20fighting%20in%20a%20built-up%20area%20during%20the%20capture%20of%20Maulvi%20Bazar%20in%20the%20Sylhet%20Sector%20during%20the%201971%20Bangladesh%20War%20and%20the%20fighting%20in%20Somalia%20alongside%20US%20forces%20in%20Mogadishu.%20Small%20infantry%20detachments%20with%20molotov%20cocktails%2C%20snipers%20and%20small%20anti-tank%20weapons%2F%20RPGs%20would%20stall%20the%20Russian%20advance.%20The%20Russian%20infantry%20was%20insufficient%20and%20with%20inexperienced%20soldiers%2C%20it%20was%20required%20to%20clear%20all%20buildings%20and%20lanes%20which%20was%20not%20possible.%20It%20appears%20that%20the%20only%20factor%20taken%20into%20consideration%20by%20the%20Russian%20general%20staff%20apart%20from%20the%20selection%20of%20Kyiv%20as%20the%20objective%20was%20the%20shock%20effect%20of%20armour%2C%20without%20analysing%20the%20holding%20power%20of%20the%20infantry%20with%20modern%20weapons%20and%20the%20ground%20factor%20of%20built-up%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20appears%20that%20the%20generals%20who%20planned%20this%20operation%20were%20selected%20for%20their%20higher%20command%20and%20staff%20duties%20based%20more%20on%20theoretical%20knowledge%20and%2C%20perhaps%2C%20favouritism%20and%20yesmanship.%20Otherwise%20the%20advice%20to%20the%20Russian%20president%20should%20have%20been%20more%20practical%20and%20candid.%20It%20was%20seen%20that%20as%20the%20war%20progressed%20many%20of%20them%20were%20deprived%20of%20their%20command%20and%20new%20commanders%20brought%20in%2C%20but%20that%20was%20too%20late.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20the%20Russians%20lost%20the%20initiative%20so%20essential%20during%20an%20offensive%20operation%20and%20enough%20time%20was%20available%20to%20President%20Zelenskyy%20to%20take%20stock%20of%20all%20fronts%20and%20re-group%20his%20forces%20to%20deal%20with%20them%2C%20as%20well%20as%20for%20NATO%20to%20assess%20and%20plan%20their%20moves.%20Also%2C%20the%20Russians%20leaned%20heavily%20on%20the%20Wagner%20Group%20to%20capture%20important%20objectives%20like%20Bakhmut%20rather%20than%20their%20own%20elite%20troops.%20They%20were%20more%20dependent%20on%20missile%20attacks%2C%20which%20can%20never%20be%20sufficient%20in%20a%20major%20war%20to%20dislodge%20the%20defender.%C2%A0%20At%20this%20point%2C%20the%20Russian%20offensive%20got%20into%20a%20stalemate%20with%20prohibitive%20casualties%20on%20their%20side%20not%20only%20of%20troops%20but%20also%20tanks%2C%20artillery%20and%20mechanised%20columns%20and%20a%20large%20fleet%20of%20helicopters.%20The%20Russian%20foreign%20minister%20then%20professed%20that%20the%20aim%20was%20limited%20to%20some%20areas%20and%20not%20the%20whole%20of%20Ukraine%20%E2%80%93%20which%20was%20understandably%20an%20acceptance%20of%20failure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaving%20lost%20the%20initiative%2C%20Russia%2C%C2%A0%20instead%20of%20going%20in%20for%20a%20negotiated%20cease%20fire%2C%20switched%20to%20missile%20attacks%20on%20civilian%20areas%20and%20the%20destruction%20of%20civilian%20infrastructure%20like%20electricity%2C%20water%20supply%2C%20hospitals%2C%20and%20schools%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20unethical%20and%20deplorable%20and%20un-soldierlike.%20The%20destruction%20of%20civilian%20infrastructure%20and%20heavy%20civilian%20casualties%20cannot%20result%20in%20a%20military%20victory.%20In%20fact%2C%20it%20hardened%20the%20resolve%20of%20Ukrainians%20to%20fight%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuspension%20of%20grain%20deals%20and%20stopping%20the%20movement%20of%20grain%20from%20Ukraine%E2%80%99s%20Odessa%20port%2C%20the%20destruction%20of%20silos%20and%20godowns%20holding%20grain%20and%20destruction%20of%20connected%20infrastructure%20is%20also%20in%20bad%20taste.%20It%20will%20not%20result%20in%20any%20benefit%20to%20the%20war%20effort%20but%20earns%20negative%20points%20and%20condemnation%20world%20over.%20Also%2C%20threatening%20ships%20only%20meant%20for%20grain%20is%20a%20retrograde%20statement%20and%20step.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20war%20also%20led%20to%20Finland%20joining%20NATO%20and%20may%20hasten%20the%20remaining%20neutral%20countries%20of%20Europe%20joining%20the%20alliance%20as%20individually%20they%20are%20not%20capable%20of%20taking%20on%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EWatch%20%7C%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Watch%20%7C%20India%E2%80%99s%20Ukraine%20Stand%20'Inconsistent%2C%20Contradictory%2C%20and%20Hypocritical'%3A%20Shashi%20Tharoor%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fwatch-indias-ukraine-stand-inconsistent-contradictory-and-hypocritical-shashi-tharoor%5C%22%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20Ukraine%20Stand%20%E2%80%98Inconsistent%2C%20Contradictory%2C%20and%20Hypocritical%E2%80%99%3A%20Shashi%20Tharoor%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20military%20front%2C%20the%20war%20has%20highlighted%20the%20importance%20of%20infantry%20as%20a%20war%20winning%20factor.%20The%20Russian%20side%20lacked%20not%20only%20sufficient%20infantry%20but%20also%20deployed%20conscripts%20with%20less%20experience%2C%20whereas%20the%20Ukrainian%20infantry%20steadfastly%20held%20the%20ground%20with%20support%20from%20limited%20armour%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20handheld%20infantry%2C%20anti-tank%20and%20anti-aircraft%20weapons.%20Drones%20too%20have%20played%20a%20major%20part%20in%20the%C2%A0%20destruction%20of%20Russian%20armour%2C%20command%20and%20communication%20centres%20and%20some%20pinpointed%20objectives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20Beijing%20has%20supported%20Russia%20selectively%2C%20it%20has%20also%20projected%20itself%20as%20a%20peace-broker.%20China%20would%20not%20like%20to%20enhance%20the%20capabilities%20of%20a%20neighbour%20%E2%80%93%20for%20obvious%20reasons%20but%20may%20also%20have%20considered%20the%20%E2%80%98positive%E2%80%99%20consequences%20of%20Putin%E2%80%99s%20actions%2C%20such%20as%C2%A0%20keeping%20the%20US%20embroiled%20in%20Europe%20and%20reducing%20its%20effectiveness%20on%20the%20Taiwan%20front.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20war%20which%20the%20Russians%20expected%20to%20be%20a%20swift%2C%20short%20operation%20is%20now%20more%20than%20a%20year%20old%2C%20with%20no%20tangible%20end%20in%20sight.%20President%20Putin%20has%20rejected%20diplomatic%20and%20other%20methods%20of%20ending%20the%20war%2C%20more%20out%20of%20ego%20rather%20than%20realties%20on%20ground.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%20President%20Zelenskyy%20of%20Ukraine%20is%20sticking%20to%20his%20demand%20that%20Russia%20vacate%20all%20occupied%20areas%20before%20any%20peace%20talks%20commence.%20NATO%20has%20supplied%20all%20possible%20help%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20just%20short%20of%20formally%20declaring%20it%20a%20part%20of%20the%20organisation.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20Ukraine%20has%20now%20forced%20a%20stalemate.%20Therefore%2C%20there%20is%20an%20urgent%20need%20for%20Russia%20to%20consider%20a%20negotiated%20deal.%20NATO%20is%20much%20wiser%20from%20this%20experience%20and%20in%20any%20future%20conflict%20would%20know%20how%20to%20tackle%20it%20militarily.%20The%20Russian%20public%20is%20not%20in%20favour%20of%20prolonged%20war%20either.%20So%2C%20the%20main%20professed%20aim%20of%20Ukraine%20not%20joining%20NATO%20is%20already%20lost%20and%20short%20of%20a%20formal%20proclamation%2C%20in%20actual%20terms%20NATO%20is%20already%20there.%20The%20Black%20Sea%20is%20still%20open%20for%20everybody%20and%20Ukrainian%20wheat%20will%20keep%20moving%20out%2C%20albeit%20under%20an%20agreement%20or%20otherwise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20a%20ceasefire%20should%20be%20proclaimed.%20One%20option%20could%20be%20for%20Russia%20to%20hand%20over%20the%20area%20under%20its%20control%20to%20a%20peace%20force%20composed%20of%20Indian%2C%20South%20East%20Asian%20and%20African%20troops%2C%20as%20matters%20move%20on%20to%20the%20negotiating%20table.%20We%20have%20seen%20a%20number%20of%20African%20leaders%20take%20the%20initiative%20in%20pushing%20for%20a%20ceasefire.%20India%20has%20influence%20and%20clout%20with%20both%20Russia%20and%20the%20big%20powers%20backing%20Ukraine%20and%20the%20world%20needs%20our%20leadership%20in%20deeds%20rather%20than%20mere%20words.%20It%20is%20time%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20and%20external%20affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%20involved%20themselves%20in%20the%20search%20for%20a%20sustainable%20peace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBrigadier%20Surinder%20Singh%20(retired)%20is%20a%20war%20veteran%20and%20commanded%20a%20brigade%20in%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20Sector.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693376861000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28161248%2FFJIXugOXoAMKMh-.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Findia-needs-to-move-from-mouthing-platitudes-for-peace-to-helping-russia-and-ukraine-broker-peace%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Russia%20has%20failed%20in%20its%20primary%20objectives%20and%20the%20Russian%20public%20does%20not%20support%20a%20prolonged%2C%20endless%20war.%20That%20is%20why%20countries%20like%20India%20must%20tell%20Putin%20it%20is%20time%20to%20accept%20a%20ceasefire%20and%20for%20peacekeepers%C2%A0to%20hold%20the%20peace%20while%20Moscow%20and%20Kyiv%20work%20out%20a%20long-term%20agreement.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Findia-needs-to-move-from-mouthing-platitudes-for-peace-to-helping-russia-and-ukraine-broker-peace%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Reliance%20in%20talks%20with%20head%20hunters%20to%20find%20CEO%20for%20Jio's%20Insurance%20biz%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693376860000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-08%2F22%2Ffull%2F1692674822-4327.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Freliance-in-talks-with-head-hunters-to-find-ceo-for-jio-insurance-123083000276_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ex