Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fdelhi%2Famid-confusion-rakshabandhan-to-be-celebrated-on-two-days%2Farticleshow%2F103189965.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Like%20last%20year%2C%20this%20year%20too%2C%20festival%20of%20Rakshabandhan%20will%20be%20celebrated%20on%20two%20days%20(August%2030%20and%2031)%20due%20to%20confusion%20over%20the%20most%20auspicious%20time%20to%20tie%20rakhi.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TNN%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A32%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fdelhi%2Famid-confusion-rakshabandhan-to-be-celebrated-on-two-days%2Farticleshow%2F103189965.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Today%E2%80%99s%20India%20Has%20All%20the%20Markers%20of%20a%20Failing%20Democracy.%20But%20the%20Situation%20Is%20Not%20Irreversible.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F29175956%2FScreenshot-2023-08-29-at-5.59.06-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20following%20is%20the%20full%20text%20of%20the%20Borker%20Memorial%20Lecture%20delivered%20by%20Justice%20(Retired)%20A.P.%20Shah%2C%20titled%20%E2%80%98My%20Vision%20for%20India%3A%202047%20A.D%E2%80%99%20on%20August%2024%2C%202023.%20The%20lecture%20honours%20the%20distinguished%20civil%20servant%20and%20public%20educator%20D.S.%20Borker.%20In%20the%20lecture%2C%20the%20former%20Delhi%20high%20court%20judge%20says%20India%20today%20has%20all%20the%20markers%20of%20a%20failing%20democracy%20and%20elected%20autocracy%2C%20with%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20efforts%20to%20establish%20a%20Hindu%20rashtra%20thoroughly%20underway.%20However%2C%20he%20says%20hatred%20and%20divisiveness%2C%20whether%20in%20politics%20or%20society%2C%20cannot%20survive%20for%20long.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20text%20has%20been%20edited%20lightly%20for%20style%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGood%20evening%2C%20everyone.%20Thank%20you%20for%20being%20here%2C%20and%20thanks%20also%20to%20the%20Borker%20family%20for%20inviting%20me%20to%20deliver%20the%20Borker%20Memorial%20Lecture.%20Shri%20D.S.%20Borker%20was%20a%20distinguished%20civil%20servant%20and%20public%20educator%20who%20was%20always%20focused%20on%20the%20future%2C%20and%20especially%20the%20youth%20of%20our%20country.%20It%20is%20an%20honour%20to%20be%20here%20to%20celebrate%20the%20legacy%20of%20a%20visionary%20like%20Shri%20Borker%2C%20and%20also%20push%20ourselves%20to%20think%20more%20like%20him%2C%20for%20what%20lies%20ahead%20for%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFittingly%2C%20the%20Borker%20Memorial%20Lecture%20is%20forward-looking%20and%20asks%20speakers%20to%20speak%20on%20one%20subject%20only%2C%20that%20is%2C%20%E2%80%9CMy%20Vision%20for%20India%3A%202047%20AD%E2%80%9D.%20This%20topic%20asks%20a%20question%20which%20is%20at%20once%20deeply%20personal%20and%20deeply%20political.%20It%20asks%20me%20what%20%3Cem%3Emy%3C%2Fem%3E%20vision%20is%2C%20but%20also%20what%20my%20vision%20is%20%3Cem%3Efor%3C%2Fem%3E%20India.%20Addressing%20this%20in%20any%20meaningful%20way%20requires%20engaging%20with%20the%20past%2C%20present%20and%20future%20all%20at%20once.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%3Ci%3EGlimpse%20of%20the%20current%20crisis%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E2023%20is%20a%20particularly%20interesting%20year%20for%20this%20discussion.%20India%20is%20over%2075%20years%20into%20life%20as%20a%20constitutional%20democracy%2C%20and%20enough%20markers%20%E2%80%93%20social%2C%20political%2C%20economic%20%E2%80%93%20exist%20to%20examine%20whether%20our%20constitutional%20promises%20have%20been%20sufficiently%20secured%20and%20upheld%20for%20all%20our%20people.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20are%20certain%20things%20about%20this%20country%20I%20am%20extremely%20proud%20of%2C%20such%20as%20the%20transformative%20contributions%20made%20in%20the%20fields%20of%20science%20and%20technology%2C%20whether%20it%20is%20space%20science%2C%20or%20IT%2C%20or%20even%20the%20growth%20in%20infrastructure%20over%20the%20past%2030%20years%20especially.%20Like%20millions%20of%20Indians%2C%20my%20wife%20and%20I%20cried%20with%20joy%20when%20Chandrayaan-3%20landed%20on%20the%20moon.%20I%20remember%20our%20science%20teacher%20in%20school%2C%20a%20sort%20of%20dreamer%2C%20who%20showed%20us%20the%20world%20beyond%20the%20skies%2C%20introducing%20us%20to%20NASA%2C%20and%20the%20Indian%20space%20projects%20led%20by%20Homi%20Bhabha%20and%20Vikram%20Sarabhai.%20%5BThe%5D%20moon%20landing%20%5Bon%20August%2023%5D%20was%20an%20emotional%20moment%20for%20all%20of%20us.%20But%20I%20am%20deeply%20troubled%20by%20many%20other%20things.%20If%20you%20look%20deeper%2C%20it%20seems%20to%20me%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20society%20and%20institutions%20are%20in%20a%20state%20of%20unprecedented%20disruption%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20a%20crisis.%20Some%20argue%20that%20democracy%20here%20is%20dying%20a%20slow%20death.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDemocratic%20principles%20have%20not%20been%20directly%20or%20explicitly%20subverted%2C%20but%20in%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20democratic%20institutions%20and%20accountability%20mechanisms%20have%20been%20neutralised%20or%20compromised.%20There%20has%20been%20an%20insidious%20harvesting%20of%20a%20culture%20of%20hate%2C%20leading%20to%20active%20theatres%20of%20violence.%20Polarisation%20is%20unrestrained%2C%20vilifying%20minorities%2C%20with%20the%20majority%20being%20made%20to%20think%20of%20the%20other%2C%20especially%20Muslims%2C%20as%20the%20enemy%2C%20whether%20in%20Haridwar%20or%20Haryana%20or%20elsewhere.%20A%20general%20sentiment%20of%20hatred%20of%20minorities%20can%20be%20heard%2C%20seen%20and%20felt%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20how%20did%20we%20reach%20here%3F%20How%20did%20we%20manage%20to%20get%20it%20so%20wrong%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPhilosophers%2C%20politicians%2C%20public%20intellectuals%20remind%20us%20that%20where%20we%20are%20today%20is%20usually%20because%20we%20have%20forgotten%20the%20past.%20The%20philosopher%20Santayana%20had%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThose%20who%20cannot%20remember%20the%20past%20are%20condemned%20to%20repeat%20it%E2%80%9D.%20Similarly%2C%20Churchill%20wrote%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthose%20that%20failed%20to%20learn%20from%20history%20are%20doomed%20to%20repeat%20it%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20same%20spirit%2C%20asking%20what%20one%E2%80%99s%20vision%20for%20India%20is%20requires%20considering%20what%20the%20idea%20of%20India%20was%20in%20the%20first%20place.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F03%2F11121816%2FScreen-Shot-2021-03-11-at-12.17.56-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22781%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F03%2F11121816%2FScreen-Shot-2021-03-11-at-12.17.56-PM.png%20781w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F03%2F11121816%2FScreen-Shot-2021-03-11-at-12.17.56-PM-300x179.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-515704%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22465%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentative%20image.%20Photo%3A%20Sean%20Ellis%2FFlickr%20(CC%20BY%202.0)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EBackdrop%20to%20the%20making%20of%20the%20constitution%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cb%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%201947%2C%20the%20social%2C%20political%2C%20cultural%20scene%20was%20as%20crowded%20and%20as%20messy%20as%20you%20would%20imagine%20it%20to%20be.%20India%E2%80%99s%20nationalist%20movement%20was%20born%20in%20a%20melting%20pot%20of%20shifting%20cultural%20values%20and%20increasing%20pressures%20for%20social%20and%20political%20change%2C%20where%20thinkers%20set%20out%20to%20define%20their%20idea%20of%20free%20India%2C%20and%20find%20their%20meaning%20of%20nationalism.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20word%20%E2%80%9Cnationalism%E2%80%9D%20encompasses%20many%20meanings%20%E2%80%93%20it%20can%20mean%20progressive%2C%20revolutionary%2C%20pro-people%2C%20or%20even%20regressive%20or%20jingoistic%20nationalism.%20Hitler%E2%80%99s%20nationalism%2C%20while%20different%20from%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%2C%20was%20a%20kind%20of%20nationalism%2C%20nevertheless.%20But%20we%20can%20safely%20say%20that%20the%20Indian%20concept%20of%20nationalism%20emerged%20in%20opposition%20to%20the%20imperialist%20British%20state%2C%20an%20%E2%80%9Canti-colonial%E2%80%9D%20nationalism%2C%20where%20identity%20was%20not%20tied%20to%20religion%2C%20caste%2C%20or%20language%2C%20but%20to%20a%20unified%20demand%20for%20freedom.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEfforts%20to%20define%20free%20India%20tried%20to%20assimilate%20positive%20aspects%20of%20Western%20and%20Indian%20traditions.%20Notably%2C%20thinkers%20like%20Vivekananda%2C%20Tagore%20and%20Aurobindo%2C%20besides%20Gandhi%2C%20of%20course%2C%20in%20their%20own%20ways%2C%20arrived%20at%20ideas%20of%20free%20India%2C%20responding%20to%20a%20dynamic%20socio-cultural%20milieu%2C%20and%20a%20frenetic%20pace%20of%20political%20change.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EVivekananda%2C%C2%A0%20for%20instance%2C%20said%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSeveral%20dangers%20are%20in%20the%20way%20and%20one%20is%20that%20of%20the%20extreme%20conception%20that%20we%20are%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20people%20in%20the%20world.%20With%20all%20my%20love%20for%20India%20and%20with%20all%20my%20patriotism%2C%20and%20veneration%20for%20the%20ancients%2C%20I%20cannot%20but%20think%20that%20we%20have%20to%20learn%20many%20things%20from%20other%20nations.%20We%20must%20be%20always%20ready%20to%20sit%20at%20the%20feet%20of%20all%2C%20for%20mark%20you%2C%20every%20one%20can%20teach%20us%20great%20lessons.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETagore%E2%80%99s%20concern%20was%20%E2%80%9CThe%20suddenness%20with%20which%20we%20stepped%20%E2%80%A6%20into%20another%20%5Bera%5D%20with%20its%20new%20meaning%20and%20values!%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20that%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20was%20still%20no%20deep%20awareness%20of%20human%20rights%2C%20human%20dignity%2C%20class%20equality%E2%80%9D.%20For%20Aurobindo%2C%20%E2%80%9CLiberty%20and%20equality%E2%80%9D%20were%20%E2%80%9Cwatchwords%20of%20humanity%2C%E2%80%9D%20which%20could%20%E2%80%9C%5Bremould%5D%20nations%20and%20Governments.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20thinkers%20exhibit%20consistent%20motifs%20of%20what%20free%20India%20must%20strive%20for%20%E2%80%93%20social%20and%20political%20freedoms%2C%20equality%2C%20fraternity%2C%20and%20dignity%E2%80%A6%20They%20also%20recognised%20certain%20obstacles%20that%20lay%20in%20wait%2C%20such%20as%20orthodoxy%20and%20superstition%2C%20leading%20to%20discriminations%20like%20untouchability.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Hindu%20revivalists%20relied%20on%20an%20imagined%20glorious%20Indian%20past%20as%20the%20template%20for%20its%20future.%20I%20must%20mention%20as%20an%20aside%20that%20my%20grandfather%20was%20the%20president%20of%20the%20Hindu%20Mahasabha%20in%20the%201940s.%20The%20earliest%20literature%20I%20read%20as%20a%20young%20boy%20in%20school%20was%20V.D.%20Savarkar%2C%20when%20I%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20his%20initial%20poetry%2C%20though%20his%20later%20poems%20became%20highly%20Sanskritised%20and%20tedious%20to%20read.%20Savarkar%E2%80%99s%20poetry%20was%20one%20of%20my%20subjects%20in%20graduation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESavarkar%20envisaged%20a%20nation%20under%20Hindu%20rule%2C%20a%20Hindu%20Rashtra%2C%20in%20Akhand%20Bharat%20(a%20United%20India).%20It%20was%20premised%20on%20the%20belief%20that%20only%20Hindus%20can%20claim%20India%E2%80%99s%20territory%20as%20the%20land%20of%20their%20ancestry%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Epitru%20bhoomi%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%20of%20their%20religion%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Epunya%20bhoomi.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3EMuslims%20and%20Christians%20are%20foreigners%2C%20for%20they%20are%20not%20indigenous%20and%20their%20religion%20originated%20in%20a%20separate%20land.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Later%2C%20M.S.%20Golwalkar%20wrote%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20foreign%20races%20in%20Hindusthan%20%E2%80%A6%20must%20lose%20their%20separate%20existence%20to%20merge%20in%20the%20Hindu%20race%2C%20or%20may%20stay%20in%20the%20country%2C%20only%20subordinated%20to%20the%20Hindu%20Nation%2C%20claiming%20nothing%2C%20deserving%20no%20privileges%2C%20far%20less%20any%20preferential%20treatment%20%E2%80%93%20not%20even%20citizens%E2%80%99%20rights.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHindutva%20forces%20were%20generally%20suspicious%20of%20secular%20ideas.%20Instead%2C%20Savarkar%20justified%20Hitler%E2%80%99s%20treatment%20of%20Jews%2C%20and%20B.S.%20Moonje%20even%20met%20Mussolini%20in%20Italy.%20But%20such%20ideas%20were%20at%20best%20marginal%20in%20the%20independence%20movement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbenjamin-zachariah-fascism-sangh-parivar%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98India%20Has%20The%20Longest%20Running%20Fascist%20Movement%20in%20the%20World%20%E2%80%93%20The%20RSS%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ETryst%20with%20destiny%3A%20The%20peremptory%20values%20emerging%20from%20the%20constitution%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAgainst%20this%20background%2C%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20started%20to%20write%20a%20Constitution%20to%20serve%20multitudes%20of%20people.%20It%20chose%20an%20inclusive%20path%2C%20not%20just%20for%20moral%2C%20but%20also%20practical%20reasons.%20This%20path%20ensured%20India%20could%20transition%20to%20a%20nation%20where%20diverse%20groups%20peacefully%20coexisted.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENote%20that%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20made%20contrarian%20ideological%20choices%20in%201947%2C%20and%20we%20consciously%20rejected%20a%20religious%20state.%20Vallabhbhai%20Patel%2C%20in%20a%20letter%20of%201947%2C%20famously%20wrote%2C%20that%20it%20would%20not%20be%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9Cpossible%20to%20consider%20Hindustan%20as%20a%20Hindu%20state%20with%20Hinduism%20as%20the%20State%20religion.%20We%20must%20not%20forget%20that%20there%20are%20other%20minorities%20whose%20protection%20is%20our%20primary%20responsibility.%20The%20State%20must%20exist%20for%20all%20irrespective%20of%20caste%20or%20creed.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOur%20constitution%20makers%20thus%20chose%20a%20republican%20form%20of%20democracy%20to%20bring%20together%20a%20multi-cultural%20society%2C%20where%20diversity%20could%20breathe%20and%20thrive.%20But%20there%20were%20two%20expectations%2C%20each%20from%20the%20state%20and%20people.%20The%20state%2C%20especially%20its%20enforcement%20wing%2C%20had%20to%20shed%20its%20colonial%20habits%20(of%20treating%20the%20citizen%20always%20as%20a%20servile%20subject).%20And%20minority%20faith%20communities%20had%20to%20become%20assured%20of%20their%20well-being%20in%20society%20and%20not%20be%20inward-looking%2C%20dependent%20in%20turn%20on%20a%20majority%20not%20unleashing%20majoritarian%20impulses%2C%20to%20slowly%20foster%20fraternal%20relations%20with%20each%20other%20%E2%80%93%20and%20together%20arrive%20at%20a%20path%20to%20social%20democracy.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20constitution%20was%20firmly%20secular%20and%20egalitarian%2C%20declaring%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20state%20shall%20not%20discriminate%20against%20any%20citizen%20on%20grounds%20only%20of%20religion%2C%20race%2C%20caste%2C%20sex%2C%20place%20of%20birth%2C%20or%20any%20of%20them.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Constituent%20Assembly%20dwelt%20upon%20the%20idea%20of%20secularism%20considerably.%20H.V.%20Kamath%20proposed%20that%20the%20Preamble%20begin%20with%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20name%20of%20God%E2%80%9D%2C%20but%20many%20opposed%20this.%20Hridaynath%20Kunzru%20said%20that%20invoking%20the%20name%20of%20God%20was%20inconsistent%20with%20the%20freedom%20of%20religion%20and%20was%20instead%20reflective%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnarrow%2C%20sectarian%20spirit%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Constituent%20Assembly%2C%20incidentally%20comprising%20an%20over%2080%25%20Hindu%20majority%2C%20embedded%20secularism%20in%20the%20constitution%20in%20multiple%20ways%2C%20through%20fundamental%20rights%20protecting%20religious%20freedoms%2C%20through%20a%20judiciary%20that%20would%20arbiter%20religious%20concerns%2C%20and%20through%20an%20Indian%20model%20of%20secularism%2C%20distinct%20from%20the%20western%20church-state%20model%2C%20respecting%20religious%20diversity%2C%20and%20promoting%20tolerance%20and%20plurality.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Constituent%20Assembly%20also%20factored%20in%20the%20great%20deprivation%20facing%20India%E2%80%99s%20poor%2C%20illiterate%2C%20and%20highly%20under-nourished%2C%20for%20whom%20the%20Directive%20Principles%20framework%20was%20created%2C%20with%20a%20range%20of%20economic%20and%20social%20rights%2C%20and%20mandating%20the%20State%20to%20abide%20with%20them%20wholly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EClosely%20connected%20to%20this%20was%20the%20stark%20social%20and%20economic%20inequality%20in%20the%20country.%20Dr%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%20understood%20this%20well.%20To%20him%2C%20a%20healthy%20democracy%20meant%20more%20than%20just%20an%20independent%20judiciary%20or%20a%20free%20and%20fair%20electoral%20process.%20With%20great%20foresight%2C%20he%20cautioned%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20that%20political%20democracy%20would%20be%20inadequate%20if%20inequalities%20remained.%20In%C2%A0%201949%2C%20he%20said%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9COn%20the%2026th%20of%20January%201950%2C%20we%20are%20going%20to%20enter%20into%20a%20life%20of%20contradictions.%20In%20politics%20we%20will%20have%20equality%20and%20in%20social%20and%20economic%20life%20we%20will%20have%20inequality.%20In%20politics%20we%20will%20be%20recognising%20the%20principle%20of%20one%20man%20one%20vote%20and%20one%20vote%20one%20value.%20In%20our%20social%20and%20economic%20life%2C%20we%20shall%2C%20by%20reason%20of%20our%20social%20and%20economic%20structure%2C%20continue%20to%20deny%20the%20principle%20of%20one%20man%20one%20value.%20How%20long%20shall%20we%20continue%20to%20live%20this%20life%20of%20contradictions%3F%20How%20long%20shall%20we%20continue%20to%20deny%20equality%20in%20our%20social%20and%20economic%20life%3F%20If%20we%20continue%20to%20deny%20it%20for%20long%2C%20we%20will%20do%20so%20only%20by%20putting%20our%20political%20democracy%20in%20peril.%20We%20must%20remove%20this%20contradiction%20at%20the%20earliest%20possible%20moment%20or%20else%20those%20who%20suffer%20from%20inequality%20will%20blow%20up%20the%20structure%20of%20political%20democracy%20which%20this%20Assembly%20has%20so%20laboriously%20built%20up.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20also%20said%20that%20in%20order%20to%20%E2%80%9Cmaintain%20democracy%2C%20not%20merely%20in%20form%2C%20but%20also%20in%20fact%E2%80%9D%2C%20we%20needed%20to%20%E2%80%9Cmake%20our%20political%20democracy%20a%20social%20democracy%20as%20well%E2%80%9D.%20He%20further%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWithout%20equality%2C%20liberty%20would%20produce%20the%20supremacy%20of%20the%20few%20over%20the%20many.%20Equality%20without%20liberty%20would%20kill%20individual%20initiative.%20Without%20fraternity%2C%20liberty%20and%20equality%20could%20not%20pick%20up%20a%20natural%20course%20of%20things.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EArguably%2C%20India%20today%20celebrates%20at%20best%20only%20a%20political%20democracy.%20We%20forget%20the%20other%20dimensions%20of%20the%20true%20democracy%20Ambedkar%20had%20hoped%20India%20would%20have%2C%20of%20economic%20and%20social%20democracy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmbedkar%20was%20also%20deeply%20wedded%20to%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20democratic%20state%20run%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20morality.%20Without%20morality%2C%20he%20believed%2C%20the%20state%20would%20be%20reduced%20to%20anarchy.%20This%20is%20how%20courts%20have%20also%20developed%20the%20concept%20of%20%E2%80%9Cconstitutional%20morality%E2%80%9D%2C%20that%20is%2C%20to%20respect%20and%20abide%20by%20what%20is%20contained%20in%20the%20constitution%20in%20spirit%20and%20not%20merely%20in%20letter.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F14124741%2FIMG_1874-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F14124741%2FIMG_1874-1.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F14124741%2FIMG_1874-1-300x120.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F14124741%2FIMG_1874-1-1024x410.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-648515%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EMissed%20years%3A%20Failed%20constitutional%20promises%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Indian%20experiment%20did%20not%20get%20off%20to%20a%20great%20start.%20The%20constitution%20was%20only%20a%20map%20to%20secure%20an%20equal%20and%20prosperous%20future%20for%20all.%20India%20still%20needed%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98build%20the%20Nation%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Certainly%2C%20power%20structures%20have%20been%20irreversibly%20pushed%20towards%20inclusiveness.%20But%20some%20complacency%20has%20also%20allowed%20the%20extremist%20right%20wing%20to%20inch%20into%20governance%20and%20everyday%20life.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20begin%20with%20how%20political%20power%20has%20widened.%20Undoubtedly%2C%20the%20Mandal%20agitation%2C%20and%20regional%20parties%20have%20secured%20greater%20participation%20of%20Dalits%20and%20other%20oppressed%20castes%20in%20politics%2C%20in%20states%20and%20at%20the%20Centre.%20Constitutional%20amendments%20have%20helped%20decentralise%20governance%20structures%20at%20grassroots%20levels%2C%20and%20introduced%20mandatory%20panchayat%20and%20%3Cem%3Enagar%20mahapalika%3C%2Fem%3E%20elections%2C%20with%20reservations%20for%20women%20and%20SCs%2FSTs.%20Implementation%20may%20be%20imperfect%2C%20but%20neglected%20segments%20that%20form%20society%E2%80%99s%20majority%20%E2%80%93%20women%2C%20oppressed%20castes%20%E2%80%93%20have%20gained%20political%20voice%20and%20decision-making%20authority%2C%20fundamentally%20altering%20power%20structures.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20also%20inherited%20a%20strong%20culture%20of%20people%E2%80%99s%20movements%20from%20the%20freedom%20struggle.%20Many%20from%20the%20earlier%20generations%2C%20Midnight%E2%80%99s%20children%20as%20they%20are%20sometimes%20called%2C%20committed%20themselves%20to%20the%20nation-building%20project.%20Mass%20movements%20%E2%80%93%20the%20MKSS%2C%20Narmada%20Bachao%20Andolan%2C%20the%20Chipko%20movement%2C%20the%20various%20movements%20around%20women%E2%80%99s%20rights%20%E2%80%93%20effectively%20impacted%20law%20and%20policy-making%20towards%20people%E2%80%99s%20rights.%20Examples%20are%20the%20Panchayat%20Extension%20to%20Scheduled%20Areas%20(PESA)%20Act%2C%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%2C%20food%20security%20laws%2C%20the%20Right%20to%20Education%2C%20MNREGA%2C%20mid-day%20meal%20schemes%2C%20the%20Forest%20Rights%20Act.%20Again%2C%20implementation%20may%20be%20imperfect%2C%20but%20these%20are%20hopefully%20here%20to%20stay.%20Every%20political%20party%20has%20had%20to%20acknowledge%20that%20for%20the%20Indian%20state%20to%20remain%20legitimate%2C%20social%20welfare%20is%20a%20must.%20However%2C%20these%20guarantees%20are%20also%20being%20chipped%20away%2C%20which%20should%20be%20of%20grave%20concern%20to%20us.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUltimately%2C%20India%20is%20a%20story%20of%20deep%20contradictions.%20A%20middle%20class%20has%20grown%2C%20but%20most%20of%20our%20population%20remains%20vulnerable%2C%20with%20basic%20public%20goods%20being%20mostly%20deficient%2C%20like%20education%2C%20health%2C%20livelihood%2C%20employment%2C%20or%20a%20clean%20environment.%20India%E2%80%99s%20human%20development%20indicators%20are%20languishing%20barely%20higher%20than%20that%20of%20sub-Saharan%20Africa.%20While%20rhetoric%20and%20propaganda%20over%20the%20decades%20may%20have%20swayed%20us%2C%20in%20truth%2C%20as%20economist%20Ashoka%20Mody%20has%20pointed%20out%2C%20every%20Indian%20government%2C%20from%20Nehru%20to%20Modi%2C%20has%20failed%20this%20country%20in%20delivering%20basic%20public%20goods.%20Unless%20this%20is%20reversed%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20faces%20a%20future%20of%20mass%20unemployment%20with%20consequent%20discontent%20and%20even%2C%20perhaps%2C%20social%20violence.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20has%20led%20to%20a%20precipitating%20fall%20in%20public%20trust%20for%20formal%20institutions%20%E2%80%93%20courts%2C%20parliament%2C%20police%2C%20and%20civilian%20bureaucracy.%20It%20started%20with%20the%20Emergency%20years%2C%20which%20were%20unquestionably%20the%20Dark%20Ages%20for%20India.%20This%20was%20when%20the%20Indian%20playbook%20for%20authoritarianism%20was%20first%20written%2C%20a%20terrifying%20trailer%20for%20times%20to%20come.%20Amity%20in%20society%20deteriorated%2C%20and%20fissures%20along%20religious%20and%20caste%20lines%20deepened.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENow%2C%20I%20see%20the%20rise%20of%20illiberal%20and%20communal%20forces%20in%20India%2C%20that%20is%20made%20possible%2C%20in%20part%2C%20by%20disillusionment%20with%20successive%20governments.%20This%20is%20compounded%20by%20a%20legal%20architecture%20that%20is%20permissive%20of%20abuse%2C%20and%20prejudices%20inherent%20in%20society.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwhat-is-this-new-india-that-bjp-speaks-of%5C%22%3EWhat%20Is%20This%20%E2%80%98New%20India%E2%80%99%20That%20BJP%20Speaks%20of%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20rise%20of%20the%20right-wing%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20worrying%20resurgence%20of%20communalism%2C%20a%20deeply%20divisive%20form%20of%20religious%20nationalism%2C%20has%20powerful%20political%20backing%2C%20seeking%20to%20realise%20Sarvakar%E2%80%99s%20ideal%20%E2%80%9CHindu%20Rashtra%2C%20Hindu%20Jati%20(race)%20and%20Hindu%20Sanskriti.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20a%20thought%20exercise%2C%20though%2C%20let%20us%20test%20Savarkar%E2%80%99s%20theory.%20He%20believed%20that%20those%20whose%20sacred%20sites%20lie%20outside%20India%E2%80%99s%20geographical%20limits%20cannot%20be%20Indian%20or%20would%20be%20lesser%20citizens.%20Thus%2C%20Muslims%20and%20Christians%20would%20be%20foreigners%2C%20not%20indigenous%20to%20India%2C%20because%20their%20religion%20originated%20elsewhere.%20By%20corollary%2C%20then%2C%20as%20Rajmohan%20Gandhi%20in%20a%20previous%20Borker%20lecture%20explained%2C%20the%20millions%20of%20Hindus%20who%20live%20outside%20India%20cannot%20be%20Americans%2C%20or%20South%20Africans%2C%20or%20Fijians.%20%3Cem%3EAll%3C%2Fem%3E%20Indians%20abroad%20would%20be%20second-class%20citizens%20there.%20By%20extension%2C%20%3Cem%3Eall%3C%2Fem%3E%20Christians%20and%20Muslims%20living%20outside%20their%20Holy%20Lands%20would%20be%20suspect%20too.%20That%20the%20Savarkar%20vision%20is%20outrageously%20outdated%20is%20putting%20it%20mildly.%20People%20are%20not%20defined%20by%20geography%20or%20religion%2C%20just%20as%20democratic%20nations%20are%20not%20chambers%20of%20rigid%20uniformity%20or%20isolation.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENevertheless%2C%20this%20clamorous%20view%20is%20being%20propounded%20in%20India%20today%20still%2C%20to%20a%20point%20where%20minorities%20are%20living%20lives%20in%20fear%2C%20and%20with%20some%20truth%2C%20that%20their%20citizenship%20has%20been%20reduced%20to%20second-class%20existence.%20Incidents%20like%20those%20that%20took%20place%20in%20Nuh%20and%20even%20in%20Delhi%2C%20perpetuate%20this%20feeling.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EExtrajudicial%20tools%20like%20encounter%20killings%2C%20panchayat%20bans%20on%20traders%20from%20minority%20communities%2C%20and%20%E2%80%98bulldozer%20politics%E2%80%99%20have%20exacerbated%20this%20situation.%20This%20last%20situation%20is%20something%20that%20particularly%20troubles%20me.%20The%20bulldozer%20today%20has%20become%20a%20symbol%20of%20power%2C%20that%20is%20wielded%20without%20legal%20sanction%20or%20authority.%20Innocent%20lives%20and%20livelihoods%20are%20lost%2C%20with%20no%20respite%20in%20sight.%20It%20involves%20the%20physical%20demolition%20of%20homes%20on%20the%20mere%20suspicion%20that%20%E2%80%9Cmaybe%20someone%20living%20there%20has%20participated%20in%20riots%20or%20indulged%20in%20some%20form%20of%20criminal%20violence%20or%20activity%E2%80%9D.%20Beyond%20the%20act%20of%20demolition%2C%20there%20are%20devastating%20consequences%20for%20entire%20families%20and%20communities.%20Who%20will%20help%20them%20rebuild%20their%20destroyed%20lives%20%E2%80%93%20not%20just%20their%20homes%3F%20Does%20the%20state%20realise%20the%20grave%20implications%20of%20its%20machismo%20display%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28163515%2F12.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28163515%2F12.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28163515%2F12-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28163515%2F12-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670281%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFamilies%20in%20Mathura%20live%20under%20plastic%20and%20paper%20roofs%20with%20their%20children%20after%20their%20houses%20were%20demolished.%20Photo%3A%20Atul%20Howale%2FThe%20Wire%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThose%20responsible%20for%20maintaining%20the%20rule%20of%20law%2C%20like%20courts%2C%20remain%20silent%20spectators.%20If%20I%20am%20not%20mistaken%2C%20there%20has%20not%20been%20a%20single%20case%20where%20innocent%20victims%20have%20found%20justice.%20When%2C%20occasionally%2C%20a%20bench%2C%20like%20in%20the%20Punjab%20and%20Haryana%20high%20court%2C%20suo%20moto%20questions%20the%20strong%20arm%20of%20the%20state%2C%20the%20case%20itself%20is%20taken%20away.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20same%20story%20has%20played%20out%20in%20the%20case%20of%20hate%20speeches%20as%20well.%20Politicians%20and%20politically-backed%20media%20outlets%20routinely%20foster%20communal%20hate.%20State%20and%20local%20governments%20are%20either%20complicit%20or%20inert.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20tried%20to%20curb%20hate%20speech%2C%20but%20to%20no%20avail%2C%20and%20the%20cycle%20of%20violence%20and%20hatred%20continues.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20another%20thought%20exercise%2C%20consider%20this%3A%20Hindus%20can%20never%20be%20denied%20their%20place%20in%20India.%20There%20is%20no%20evidence%20of%20the%20Hindu%20faith%20facing%20a%20crisis%20of%20any%20kind%20in%20India.%20Fantastic%20claims%20of%20disproportionate%20Muslim%20population%20growth%20and%20love%20jihad%20are%20mere%20propaganda.%20Hindu%20nationalism%2C%20Hindu%20assertion%2C%20or%20whatever%20term%20you%20prefer%2C%20will%20always%20have%20a%20place%20here%3B%20the%20right%20to%20free%20speech%20ensures%20that%20this%20voice%20exists.%20But%20when%20extremist%20right-wing%20groups%20take%20over%20and%20silence%20minorities%2C%20a%20state%20of%20hegemony%20comes%20about.%20Telling%20people%20what%20they%20can%20and%20cannot%20eat%2C%20wear%2C%20watch%2C%20or%20speak%20about%2C%20or%20whom%20they%20can%20or%20can%E2%80%99t%20marry%2C%20amounts%20to%20imposing%20a%20homogenous%20culture%20on%20non-conformists.%20In%20a%20democracy%2C%20this%20is%20a%20sure%20recipe%20for%20conflict.%20Ambedkar%20forewarned%20us%20about%20this.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20feel%20that%20the%20idea%20of%20Hindutva%2C%20as%20we%20have%20received%20it%20today%2C%20challenges%20the%20Hindu%20faith%20itself%2C%20which%20many%20consider%20a%20liberal%2C%20tolerant%2C%20and%20generous%20religion.%20Why%20is%20Hindu%20society%20largely%20silent%20about%20what%20is%20being%20perpetrated%20in%20the%20name%20of%20their%20religion%20against%20minorities%20is%20a%20question%20many%20of%20us%20might%20well%20ask%20today.%20Recall%20Vivekananda%E2%80%99s%20memorable%20words%20from%20his%201893%20Chicago%20address%2C%20where%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20believe%20not%20only%20in%20universal%20toleration%2C%20but%20we%20accept%20all%20religions%20as%20true%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20he%20was%20%E2%80%9Cproud%20to%20belong%20to%20a%20nation%20which%20had%20sheltered%20the%20persecuted%20and%20the%20refugees%20of%20all%20religions%20and%20all%20nations%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%9D.%20Should%20we%20not%20want%20to%20feel%20that%20pride%20always%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Hindutva%20movement%20is%20marked%20by%20perpetuating%20victimhood%2C%20and%20ousting%20scientific%20temper%20and%20rationality.%20Ambedkar%E2%80%99s%20warning%20on%20this%20too%20was%20prescient.%20His%20vision%20of%20democracy%20emphasized%20that%20just%20as%20rationality%20can%20counter%20propaganda%20and%20ideological%20manipulation%2C%20a%20scientific%20spirit%2C%20focusing%20on%20coherent%20arguments%20and%20clear%20evidence%2C%20can%20protect%20people%20against%20the%20arbitrary%20exercise%20of%20power.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20today%2C%20physical%20attacks%20on%20rationalists%20and%20polemical%20attacks%20on%20scientific%20spirit%20are%20being%20unleashed%2C%20with%20Narendra%20Dabholkar%2C%20M.M.%20Kalburgi%2C%20Gauri%20Lankesh%2C%20being%20some%20who%20paid%20with%20their%20lives.%20Orthodoxy%20and%20superstition%20have%20made%20a%20strong%20comeback%2C%20surprisingly%20even%20in%20the%20Indian%20Science%20Congress.%20The%202023%20Congress%20included%20claims%20that%20%3Cem%3Erangolis%3C%2Fem%3E%20could%20ward%20off%20evils.%20Previous%20editions%20have%20had%20a%20university%20vice-chancellor%20tout%20Ravana%E2%80%99s%20fleet%20of%20aircraft%2C%20and%20a%20palaeontologist%20claim%20that%20dinosaurs%20were%20created%20by%20Brahma%2C%20besides%20a%20discussion%20on%20India%20making%20test-tube%20babies%20millennia%20ago.%20Contrast%20this%20with%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20vision%20where%20he%20encouraged%20Indian%20science%20beyond%20boundaries%2C%20to%20realise%20that%20the%20sky%20is%20not%20the%20limit.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERelatedly%2C%20education%20is%20being%20reshaped%20along%20ideological%20lines%2C%20with%20changes%20galore%20in%20school%20and%20university%20syllabi.%20At%20Delhi%20University%2C%20newspaper%20reports%20suggest%20that%2C%20in%20the%20recently%20revised%20political%20science%20syllabus%2C%20teaching%20time%20given%20to%20thinkers%20like%20Gandhi%2C%20Kabir%2C%20Iqbal%2C%20Nehru%2C%20Ram%20Mohan%20Roy%2C%20Vivekanand%2C%20Tagore%20is%20sharply%20reduced%2C%20while%20time%20given%20to%20Savarkar%20and%20Hindutva%20ideology%20has%20increased.%20BJP%20governments%20tried%20to%20rewrite%20school%20history%20textbooks%20in%20the%20early%202000s.%20This%20year%2C%20they%20successfully%20removed%20much%20of%20Mughal%20history%2C%20and%20material%20on%20dissent%20and%20communal%20violence%2C%20in%20the%20NCERT%20syllabi%2C%20leading%20expert%20advisors%2C%20including%20Suhas%20Palshikar%20and%20Yogendra%20Yadav%2C%20to%20seek%20the%20removal%20of%20their%20names%20from%20the%20new%20textbooks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fncert-history-textbooks-mughals-india%5C%22%3EIf%20NCERT%20Has%20its%20Way%2C%20the%20Study%20of%20Indian%20History%20Will%20Move%20Entirely%20Outside%20of%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EAdvent%20of%20elected%20autocracy%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20believe%20that%20the%20next%20stage%20of%20the%20Hindutva%20movement%2C%20the%20birthing%20of%20the%20Hindu%20Rashtra%2C%20is%20firmly%20in%20the%20works.%20Madhu%20Dandavate%2C%20in%20the%202000%20Borker%20lecture%2C%20prophetically%20said%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6%20the%20hardliners%20of%20%E2%80%98Hindutva%E2%80%99%20who%20have%20a%20long%20term%20objective%20to%20totally%20subvert%20secular%20character%20of%20Constitution%20will%20%E2%80%A6%20work%20hard%20even%20upto%20%E2%80%A6%202047%20to%20realize%20their%20objective.%20They%20will%20intensify%20frenzy%20among%20the%20people%20against%20secularism%20by%20whipping%20up%20hatred%20against%20religious%20minorities%20and%20by%20strengthening%20%E2%80%98Hindutva%E2%80%99%20euphoria%20among%20the%20people%20and%20urging%20them%20to%20give%202%2F3%20majority%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98Hindutva%E2%80%99%20forces%20so%20that%20secularism%20can%20be%20buried.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EToday%2C%20the%20ruling%20party%20has%20acquired%20democratic%20power%20legitimately%3B%20after%20all%2C%20majority%20has%20been%20achieved%20in%20elections.%20But%2C%20having%20been%20elected%2C%20the%20government%20is%20acting%20along%20starkly%20authoritarian%20lines%2C%20extinguishing%20the%20checks%20and%20balances%20that%20characterise%20democracy.%20Watchdog%20institutions%20are%20mostly%20co-opted%2C%20while%20outliers%20are%20so%20fear-struck%20or%20paralysed%20that%20they%20fail%20to%20expose%2C%20much%20less%20check%2C%20the%20abuse%20of%20power.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20executive%20dominance%20that%20was%20set%20in%20during%20the%20Emergency%20is%20thriving.%20Except%20this%20time%2C%20the%20issue%20is%20of%20%E2%80%9Cdestination%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20where%20are%20we%20going%20as%20a%20country%3F%20Executive%20power%20is%20nurturing%20a%20political%20culture%20and%20a%20majoritarian%20society%20incompatible%20with%20the%20Constitutional%20idea%20of%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20question%20is%20%E2%80%93%20just%20because%20it%20is%20done%20through%20legitimate%20political%20means%2C%20is%20India%20still%20definitionally%20a%20democracy%3F%20I%20have%20consistently%20maintained%20that%20we%20are%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20becoming%20quite%20the%20opposite%2C%20that%20is%2C%20an%20%E2%80%98elected%20autocracy%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20the%20Indian%20constitution%2C%20to%20quote%20the%20words%20of%20legal%20academic%20Tarunabh%20Khaitan%2C%20is%20being%20killed%20by%20a%20thousand%20cuts.%20Elected%20autocrats%20weaponise%20institutions%20for%20political%20ammunition.%20Big%20media%20and%20the%20private%20sector%20are%20silenced.%20Rules%20are%20redrafted%20to%20suit%20their%20own%20interests.%20Critical%20voices%20still%20rise%20up%2C%20but%20dissenters%20and%20questioners%20end%20up%20at%20the%20receiving%20end%20of%20all%20kinds%20of%20trouble.%20In%20this%20way%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20very%20institutions%20of%20democracy%20%5Bare%20used%5D%E2%80%A6%20to%20kill%20it%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOur%20failed%20early%20years%2C%20we%20have%20seen%2C%20contributed%20to%20creating%20conditions%20favourable%20for%20the%20rise%20of%20an%20%E2%80%98elected%20autocracy%E2%80%99.%20To%20name%20a%20few%2C%20the%20almost%20militant%20social%20movement%20of%20the%20Hindutva%20right%20wing%2C%20a%20hollowed-out%20and%20discredited%20opposition%2C%20weakened%20media%20and%20courts%2C%20have%20created%2C%20in%20some%20ways%2C%20a%20perfect%20storm%20for%20the%20Indian%20state.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EToday%2C%20institutions%20are%20weakened%20in%20explicit%20and%20implicit%20ways.%20We%20see%20a%20lack%20of%20transparency%20in%20campaign%20finance%2C%20through%20the%20opaque%20system%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20(which%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20yet%20to%20adjudicate%20upon).%20We%20also%20see%20active%20efforts%20to%20dilute%20the%20autonomy%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%2C%20an%20institution%20that%20has%20been%20blatantly%20partisan%20in%20recent%20years.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20efforts%20to%20reform%20the%20chief%20election%20commissioner%E2%80%99s%20selection%20process%20were%20undone%20by%20proposing%20an%20amendment%20to%20the%20selection%20committee%E2%80%99s%20composition%2C%20removing%20the%20chief%20justice%20of%20India%2C%20nominally%2C%20an%20independent%2C%20apolitical%20voice.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInstitutions%20are%20also%20killed%20insidiously.%20Authorities%20intended%20to%20monitor%20accountability%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Lokpal%2C%20the%20Central%20Information%20Commission%2C%20the%20National%20Human%20Rights%20Commission%2C%20today%20appear%20to%20exist%20only%20on%20paper.%20The%20Lokpal%20was%20created%20with%20the%20best%20of%20intentions%2C%20and%20designed%20to%20serve%20as%20an%20ombudsman%20to%20tackle%20corruption%20amongst%20public%20functionaries.%20But%20of%20the%20thousands%20of%20complaints%20it%20has%20received%20since%20it%20was%20set%20up%2C%20the%20Lokpal%20has%20either%20not%20registered%20the%20complaints%20at%20all%2C%20or%20dismissed%20them%20outright.%20What%20purpose%20does%20it%20really%20serve%2C%20then%2C%20one%20might%20ask.%20The%20collapse%20of%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20regime%20has%20been%20perhaps%20even%20most%20spectacular.%20Meant%20as%20a%20sunshine%20law%20to%20dispel%20the%20darkness%20surrounding%20governance%20and%20policymaking%2C%20this%20path-breaking%20law%20has%20been%20virtually%20killed%20by%20not%20making%20appointments%2C%20or%20appointing%20loyalists%2C%20and%20not%20giving%20out%20information%2C%20while%20also%20enacting%20a%20tight-fisted%20data%20protection%20law.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFederal%20relations%20are%20also%20being%20destroyed%20today%2C%20through%20partisanal%20governors%20issuing%20diktats%20to%20non-BJP%20governed%20states.%20Separately%2C%20investigating%20authorities%20like%20the%20CBI%2C%20the%20ED%20and%20the%20NIA%2C%20otherwise%20expected%20to%20conduct%20non-partisan%20inquiries%2C%20are%20today%20being%20deployed%20as%20arms%20of%20government%2C%20against%20political%20oppositions%2C%20independent%20media%2C%20dissenters%E2%80%A6%20These%20are%20not%20new%20tactics%20but%20have%20been%20misused%20in%20unprecedented%20ways%20by%20the%20present%20dispensation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F07%2F26094955%2FEnforcement-Direct_ef_1200x768.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22770%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F07%2F26094955%2FEnforcement-Direct_ef_1200x768.jpg%20770w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F07%2F26094955%2FEnforcement-Direct_ef_1200x768-300x169.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-609987%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22433%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentative%20photo%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20also%20no%20media%2C%20print%20or%20electronic%2C%20worthy%20of%20being%20called%20truly%20independent%2C%20barring%20some%20exceptions.%20Indeed%2C%20the%20media%20has%20contributed%20to%20the%20growth%20of%20the%20sentiment%20of%20hatred%20in%20the%20country.%20All%20of%20these%2C%20collectively%2C%20are%20the%20markers%20of%20a%20failing%20democracy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EClosely%20connected%20to%20this%20is%20the%20clear%20pattern%20of%20the%20government%20suppressing%20dissent%20and%20criminalising%20inconvenient%20speech%20and%20expression.%20Examples%20are%20countless%2C%20such%20as%20the%20arrest%20of%20Disha%20Ravi%20for%20circulating%20a%20protest%20toolkit%3B%20arrests%20for%20questioning%20cow%20urine%20as%20a%20COVID-19%20cure%3B%20criminal%20cases%20against%20journalists%20like%20Patricia%20Mukhim%20for%20criticising%20the%20government%20in%20a%20social%20media%20post%3B%20the%20raid%20on%20activist%20Harsh%20Mander%E2%80%99s%20premises%3B%20the%20arrest%20of%20standup%20comedian%20Munawar%20Farooqi%E2%80%A6%20Internet%20and%20communication%20blackouts%20are%20routine%2C%20such%20as%20during%20the%20farmer%20protests%2C%20or%20in%20Jammu%20%26amp%3B%20Kashmir%2C%20or%20in%20Manipur.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESome%20might%20argue%20that%20there%20are%20positive%20developments%2C%20with%20new%20laws%20being%20made%2C%20and%20old%20ones%20being%20repealed.%20Do%20not%20get%20me%20wrong%3A%20India%20desperately%20needs%20new%20laws.%20We%20remain%20reliant%20on%20antiquated%20laws%20dating%20back%20to%20over%20150%20years.%20But%20instead%20of%20actually%20thinking%20through%20new%20legal%20architecture%2C%20we%20are%20being%20given%20old%20wine%20in%20new%20bottles.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20example%2C%20the%20recently%20introduced%20criminal%20codes%20%E2%80%93%20these%20were%20sprung%20upon%20an%20unsuspecting%20population%2C%20seemingly%20not%20considering%20the%20decades-long%20criminal%20law%20reform%20debate%20here.%20Bombastic%20statements%20that%20this%20is%20the%20end%20of%20the%20colonial%20legal%20legacy%20and%20that%20Macaulay%E2%80%99s%20name%20now%20stands%20erased%2C%20are%20in%20fact%20misleading.%20Most%20of%20the%20old%20laws%20in%20fact%20continue%2C%20even%20retaining%20the%20same%20language.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20complicate%20things%2C%20the%20new%20laws%20add%20extra%20layers%20of%20ambiguity%20and%20do%20not%20increase%20individual%20liberties%2C%20but%20reduce%20them%2C%20such%20as%20the%20provision%20on%20sedition.%20It%20strikes%20particularly%20that%20the%20home%20ministry%2C%20which%20is%20pushing%20for%20the%20new%20laws%2C%20believes%20that%20criminal%20reform%20simply%20means%20longer%20incarcerations%20and%20stricter%20punishments%2C%20and%20nothing%20else.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fknow-the-three-new-criminal-bills-whats-new-and-whats-old%5C%22%3EKnow%20The%20Three%20New%20Criminal%20Bills%3A%20What%E2%80%99s%20New%20and%20What%E2%80%99s%20Old%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EJudiciary%3A%20The%20last%20bastion%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20courts%2C%20so%20much%20has%20been%20said%20that%20I%20am%20not%20even%20sure%20where%20to%20begin%20or%20end%2C%20or%20what%20to%20include%20or%20leave%20out.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20delivered%20some%20exceptional%20judgments%2C%20the%20one%20on%20the%20right%20to%20privacy%20being%20a%20pathbreaking%20work%20of%20jurisprudence.%20More%20immediately%2C%20there%20have%20been%20positive%20orders%20such%20as%20those%20pertaining%20to%20Manipur%20and%20Haryana%2C%20the%20order%20on%20hate%20speech%2C%20the%20bail%20order%20in%20the%20Bhima%20Koregaon%20violence%20case.%20But%20the%20judiciary%20has%20not%20managed%20to%20effectively%20curb%20executive%20excesses%2C%20and%20there%20is%20a%20visible%2C%20general%20reluctance%20to%20hear%20big-ticket%20matters%20like%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20or%20electoral%20bonds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20compounded%20by%20a%20perceptible%20targeting%20of%20those%20fighting%20for%20justice%2C%20without%20following%20due%20process.%20Teesta%20Setalvad%E2%80%99s%20case%20is%20a%20classic%20example%20of%20this.%20Courts%20seem%20to%20be%20not%20only%20dismissing%20cases%2C%20but%20practically%20supporting%20the%20government%20in%20going%20after%20activists.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-order-teesta-setalvad%5C%22%3ECondemned%20by%20Innuendo%3A%20Some%20Questions%20on%20the%20SC%20Order%20That%20Led%20to%20Teesta%20Setalvad%E2%80%99s%20Arrest%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHuman%20rights%20defenders%20are%20regularly%20persecuted%20by%20employing%20anti-terror%20laws%2C%20and%20specifically%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20%5BUAPA%5D.%20In%20particular%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20interpretation%20of%20the%20grant%20of%20bail%20in%20the%20UAPA%20cases%20has%20upended%20the%20principle%20of%20presumption%20of%20innocence%20under%20the%20law%20in%20the%20case%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENIA%20vs%20Zahoor%20Ahmad%20Shah%20Watali%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Now%2C%20courts%20are%20to%20presume%20the%20prosecution%20case%20to%20be%20true%20and%20then%20determine%20whether%20a%20prima%20facie%20case%20is%20made%20out.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20for%20anyone%20unfortunate%20to%20have%20been%20charged%20under%20UAPA%2C%20a%20period%20of%20indefinite%20incarceration%20lies%20ahead.%20The%20UAPA%20has%20been%20particularly%20used%20and%20abused%20in%20many%20cases%2C%20including%20the%20Bhima%20Koregaon%20and%20Delhi%20riots%20cases.%20Some%20who%20were%20accused%20and%20arrested%2C%20such%20as%20Sudha%20Bharadwaj%2C%20were%20eventually%20granted%20bail%2C%20whereas%20others%20like%20Stan%20Swamy%20died%20in%20custody%2C%20without%20any%20incriminating%20evidence%20having%20been%20clearly%20identified.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20does%20not%20help%20that%20the%20high%20courts%2C%20barring%20some%20honourable%20exceptions%2C%20are%20also%20unable%20to%20discharge%20the%20kind%20of%20truly%20independent%20role%20they%20had%20in%20the%20past.%20I%20feel%20personally%20troubled%20by%20this%20because%20my%20own%20professional%20career%20has%20been%20tied%20to%20high%20courts.%20The%20high%20courts%20were%20once%20the%20most%20vibrant%20institutions%20in%20the%20country.%20Indeed%2C%20high%20courts%20have%20an%20enviable%20legacy%20of%20being%20among%20the%20only%20democratic%20institutions%20that%20stood%20with%20and%20for%20the%20citizens%20in%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20darkest%20days%20during%20the%20Emergency%2C%20when%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20failed%20India%E2%80%99s%20people.%20But%2C%20like%20so%20much%20of%20history%2C%20that%20legacy%20seems%20to%20have%20been%20forgotten.%20On%20occasion%2C%20such%20as%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20and%20the%20plight%20of%20migrant%20workers%2C%20high%20courts%20showed%20their%20mettle%20through%20some%20bold%20orders%20and%20directions%2C%20but%20it%20seems%20that%20this%20was%20only%20a%20momentary%20ray%20of%20hope.%20Today%2C%20it%20is%20virtually%20impossible%20to%20get%20relief%20in%20civil%20liberties%20cases%20in%20some%20high%20courts%2C%20and%20for%20even%20the%20most%20blatantly%20ridiculous%20instances%20of%20a%20misuse%20or%20arbitrary%20application%20of%20a%20draconian%20law%2C%20individuals%20have%20to%20approach%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20for%20any%20redress.%20It%20is%20also%20troubling%20to%20see%20judges%20praising%20the%20benefits%20of%20cow%20urine%20and%20cow%20dung%2C%20invoking%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EManusmriti%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20and%20speaking%20the%20majoritarian%20language.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20all%20this%2C%20though%2C%20the%20executive%20realises%20that%20the%20judiciary%20is%20the%20last%20bastion%20it%20has%20to%20overcome.%20In%20that%20respect%2C%20without%20a%20formal%20change%20in%20the%20constitution%2C%20it%20might%20be%20almost%20impossible%20to%20establish%20a%20Hindu%20Rashtra.%20This%20is%20also%20perhaps%20why%20a%20conversation%20has%20suddenly%20resumed%20around%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EKeshvananda%20Bharati%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Edecision.%20The%20statesmanship%20exhibited%20by%20the%2013-judge%20constitution%20bench%20in%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Kesavananda%20Bharati%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20where%20the%20basic%20structure%20doctrine%20was%20laid%20down%2C%20and%20judicial%20custody%20of%20the%20constitution%20reclaimed%2C%20is%20but%20one%20shining%20example%20of%20what%20the%20court%20is%20capable%20of.%20The%20judgment%20spoke%20of%20six%20crucial%20elements%20that%20made%20up%20the%20Basic%20Structure%20and%20that%20cannot%20be%20altered%2C%20that%20is%2C%20democracy%2C%20secularism%2C%20rule%20of%20law%2C%20equality%2C%20federalism%2C%20and%20judicial%20independence.%20As%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20has%20rightly%20said%2C%20this%20decision%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnorth%20star%E2%80%9D%20for%20India.%20Granville%20Austin%C2%A0%20said%20that%20the%20court%20had%20established%20itself%20as%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20logical%2C%20primary%20custodian%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20and%20%E2%80%9Cits%20interpreter%20and%20guardian.%E2%80%9D%20There%20was%20a%20promise%2C%20decades%20ago%2C%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20itself%2C%20that%20it%20would%20be%20the%20sentinel%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eon%20the%20qui%20vive%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20watchful%20guardian%20protecting%20citizens%E2%80%99%20fundamental%20rights.%20Whatever%20happened%20to%20that%20promise%2C%20I%20often%20wonder%2C%20with%20great%20disappointment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F03%2F04183653%2FSupreme-Court-sexual-assault.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221201%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F03%2F04183653%2FSupreme-Court-sexual-assault.png%201201w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F03%2F04183653%2FSupreme-Court-sexual-assault-300x131.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F03%2F04183653%2FSupreme-Court-sexual-assault-1024x448.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-514287%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22525%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPhoto%3A%20PTI%2FFlickr%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EConclusion%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYou%20might%20well%20ask%2C%20why%20I%20have%20painted%20what%20appears%20to%20be%20a%20rather%20grim%20picture%20of%20what%20India%20has%20become%20in%202023%2C%20and%20why%20I%20think%20this%20is%20important%20for%20what%20my%20vision%20of%20India%20is%20in%202047.%20Every%20day%2C%20with%20increasing%20frequency%20we%20are%20bombarded%20with%20claims%20about%20the%20achievements%20of%20the%20government%2C%20and%20how%20people%E2%80%99s%20lives%20have%20improved%20and%20how%20lives%20will%20continue%20to%20get%20better%20with%20time.%20But%20if%20we%20think%20about%20this%20rationally%2C%20with%20proper%20data%2C%20information%2C%20and%20evidence%2C%20we%20will%20be%20able%20to%20look%20past%20the%20pomp%20and%20rhetoric%20for%20what%20it%20really%20is.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EConsider%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20the%20economic%20miracle%20that%20India%20is%20being%20touted%20as%20by%20the%20present%20government.%20We%20are%20told%20to%20be%20proud%20that%20India%20is%20now%20shining%20and%20that%20our%20economy%20will%20soon%20overtake%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20and%20brightest.%20But%20a%20closer%20examination%20reveals%20that%20this%20economy%20appears%20to%20be%20shining%20only%20for%20a%20very%20few.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20major%20indices%20that%20measure%20different%20aspects%20of%20governance%2C%20India%20regularly%20shows%20up%20nearer%20to%20the%20bottom%20of%20these%20lists%20than%20the%20top.%20On%20the%20Global%20Hunger%20Index%2C%20which%20measures%20hunger%20and%20food%20security%2C%20India%20is%20presently%20ranked%20at%20107%20out%20of%20117.%20On%20the%20Environmental%20Performance%20index%2C%20which%20talks%20about%20how%20governments%20handle%20air%20and%20water%20pollution%20amongst%20other%20things%2C%20India%20has%20the%20unenvious%20position%20of%20being%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20180%20countries%20measured.%20In%20the%20human%20development%20index%2C%20the%20gender%20gap%20index%2C%20the%20multi-dimensional%20poverty%20index%2C%20India%20has%20routinely%20performed%20poorly%2C%20with%20only%20marginal%20or%20occasional%20improvements.%20Not%20only%20has%20India%20done%20poorly%20compared%20with%20itself%2C%20but%20also%20compared%20with%20its%20immediate%20and%20larger%20neighbourhoods.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20does%20this%20all%20tell%20us%3F%20I%20feel%20that%20this%20march%20towards%20creating%20a%20certain%20kind%20of%20India%2C%20has%20resulted%20in%20what%20some%20have%20called%20an%20amnesia%20about%20the%20teeming%20millions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20sad%20truth%20is%20that%20for%20many%20of%20us%2C%20the%20working%20classes%2C%20the%20lower%20middle%20and%20lower%20classes%2C%20the%20agricultural%20workers%2C%20they%20just%20do%20not%20exist.%20They%20are%20unseen%2C%20unheard%20or%20ignored%2C%20living%20substandard%20lives%2C%20left%20to%20languish%20in%20the%20dark%20alleyways%2C%20in%20scorched%20farms%2C%20in%20flooded%20hillsides%2C%20in%20parched%20villages%E2%80%A6%20But%20if%20you%20introspect%20about%20this%20a%20little%20deeply%2C%20you%20will%20realise%20they%20are%20irreplaceable%20cogs%20in%20the%20wheel%20of%20our%20democracy%2C%20just%20like%20we%20are.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENobody%20can%20contest%20that%20income%20inequality%20has%20become%20more%20stark.%20There%20appears%20to%20be%20no%20meaningful%20investment%20in%20the%20health%20and%20education%20of%20those%20who%20really%20need%20it.%20Corruption%20and%20crony%20capitalism%20are%20still%20very%20much%20prevalent%2C%20except%20with%20new%20faces%20and%20new%20names%2C%20perhaps%20more%20demonic%20than%20we%20knew%20them%20to%20be%20before.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20the%20situation%20that%20we%20are%20in%20today%20is%20not%20irreversible.%20To%20reverse%20this%2C%20we%20must%20jolt%20ourselves%20awake%20with%20a%20few%20realisations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20need%20to%20recognise%20that%20communalism%20is%20%E2%80%98not%20only%20the%20badge%20of%20a%20backward%20nation%E2%80%99%2C%20as%20Nehru%20had%20famously%20once%20said%2C%20but%20also%20that%20it%20has%20a%20limited%20shelf%20life.%20Recall%20what%20I%20had%20said%20at%20the%20start%20of%20my%20lecture%20today%2C%20that%20history%20has%20a%20lot%20to%20teach%20us.%20History%20has%20taught%20us%2C%20time%20and%20again%2C%20that%20hatred%20and%20divisiveness%2C%20whether%20in%20politics%20or%20society%2C%20cannot%20survive%20for%20long.%20Religion%20and%20religious%20groups%20might%20be%20having%20their%20day%20in%20the%20sun%2C%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20influencing%20politics%2C%20and%20economics.%20This%20is%20happening%20the%20world%20over%2C%20but%20this%20is%20also%20only%20a%20temporary%20phenomenon.%20Peacefulness%20and%20a%20peaceful%20society%20are%20the%20natural%20equilibrium%20for%20human%20society.%20Periods%20of%20war%20and%20instability%20have%20mostly%20been%20sporadic%2C%20we%20have%2C%20as%20humankind%2C%20reverted%20to%20peace%20as%20the%20default.%20In%20India%20too%2C%20we%20must%20never%20let%20go%20of%20that%20certitude%2C%20that%20we%20will%20return%20to%20peace%2C%20sooner%20than%20later.%20For%20every%20statue%20of%20Gandhi%20or%20Tagore%20being%20defaced%20or%20pulled%20down%20or%20their%20thoughts%20and%20ideas%20being%20otherwise%20devalued%20by%20the%20extremist%20right%20wing%2C%20there%20is%20a%20movement%20that%20reminds%20us%20and%20reinforces%20that%20peace%20is%20the%20only%20path%20to%20real%20progress.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20must%20also%20acknowledge%20and%20learn%20to%20value%20the%20power%20of%20knowledge.%20This%20means%20encouraging%20free%20and%20critical%20thought%20%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%20speech.%20What%20this%20means%20for%20institutional%20architecture%20is%20obvious%20%E2%80%93%20schools%20and%20universities%2C%20places%20where%20people%20go%20to%20ideate%20and%20create%2C%20and%20avenues%20through%20which%20such%20ideas%20and%20creations%20are%20consumed%2C%20such%20as%20the%20media%20%E2%80%93%20must%20be%20truly%20independent%2C%20free%20from%20fear%20or%20control.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%2C%20at%20the%20end%20of%20all%20this%2C%20you%20might%20ask%2C%20what%20is%20my%20vision%20for%20India%20of%202047%3F%20I%20would%20return%2C%20unhesitatingly%2C%20to%20history.%20The%20universal%20values%20that%20have%20survived%20since%20time%20immemorial%2C%20and%20that%20will%20survive%20for%20time%20to%20come%2C%20the%20values%20of%20truth%2C%20non-violence%2C%20compassion%20and%20kindness%20%E2%80%93%20these%20are%20what%20must%20define%20my%20India%20of%202047.%20These%20values%20must%20guide%20government%20and%20society%2C%20both.%20These%20must%20direct%20them%20to%20behave%20in%20ways%20that%20uphold%20human%20goodness%2C%20dignity%2C%20diversity%2C%20and%20inclusivity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOver%20millennia%2C%20even%20before%20India%20existed%20as%20a%20nation%2C%20the%20people%20of%20this%20subcontinent%20have%20shown%20themselves%20to%20be%20very%20resilient.%20There%20is%20so%20much%20strength%20in%20India%20and%20Indians%2C%20I%20am%20confident%20that%20we%20can%20reverse%20the%20situation%20we%20have%20found%20ourselves%20in%20today.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693362622000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F29175956%2FScreenshot-2023-08-29-at-5.59.06-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Findia-markers-failing-democracy-justice-ap-shah%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Former%20Delhi%20high%20court%20judge%20A.P.%20Shah%20says%20that%20the%20rise%20of%20illiberal%20and%20commun