nth%20stumbled%20across%20debris%20just%20below%20the%20surface%20that%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20the%20remnants%20of%20a%20historic%20wooden%20ship%20%E2%80%94%20potentially%20five%20of%20them%20%E2%80%94%20from%20World%20War%201.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20wasn't%20sure%20what%20I%20was%20really%20seeing%20but%20I%20could%20tell%20it%20was%20a%20very%20large%20vessel%2C%26quot%3B%20Bill%20Milner%20told%20the%20local%20outlet%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.khou.com%2Farticle%2Fnews%2Flocal%2Ftexas%2Fneches-river-sunken-ships%2F269-4919ff17-a3f4-4115-baab-ecd347f85b94%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKVUE%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20when%20he%20came%20across%20the%20wreckage.%20Milner%20sent%20photos%20of%20his%20find%20to%20the%20local%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icehousemuseum.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIce%20House%20Museum%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20then%20contacted%20the%20Texas%20Historical%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FTexasHistoricalCommission%2Fposts%2Fpfbid0b6Zz7xTYBCT39p8QFQBub4bSgYRt8ggdz44jZJNEpKLudDgtwQoyr5zRN2zMLTGQl%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETexas%20Historical%20Commission%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20able%20to%20confirm%20the%20ruins%20belonged%20to%20large%2C%20wooden-hull%20ships%20built%20during%20World%20War%201%20for%20the%20US%20Shipping%20Board%20Emergency%20Fleet%20Corporation%20that%20were%20later%20abandoned%20in%20the%20Neches%20and%20Sabine%20Rivers%20in%20eastern%20Texas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20amazing%20story%20of%20these%20shipwrecks%20began%20in%20WWI%2C%20when%20German%20submarines%20were%20making%20more%20than%20a%20little%20headway%20sinking%20US%20merchant%20ships%20in%20the%20Atlantic%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Ice%20House%20Museum%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Ficehousemuseum%2Fposts%2Fpfbid0KmVNi3AJKRQYAsJk2R9VSW7gXp2FfMBPyccAy8JtcpGhSSJw19ucXPBpf1UhQP4cl%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFacebook%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20a%20grave%20concern%20that%20the%20loss%20of%20these%20merchant%20ships%20would%20seriously%20impede%20their%20ability%20to%20get%20materials%20for%20the%20war%2C%20as%20well%20as%20food%20and%20other%20commodities%20needed%20by%20the%20American%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20wreckage%20shows%20one%20side%20of%20the%20hull%2C%20built%20thick%20to%20carry%20cargo%2C%20which%20metal%20spikes%20to%20hold%20the%20timber%20in%20place.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64eea78026dda200194d7ff2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221585%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThis%20photo%20of%20the%20wreckage%20shows%20one%20side%20of%20the%20hull%2C%20built%20thick%20to%20carry%20cargo%2C%20which%20metal%20spikes%20to%20hold%20the%20timber%20in%20place.%3Cp%3EBill%20Milner%2FIce%20House%20Museum%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20the%20US%20Shipping%20Board%20established%20the%20Emergency%20Fleet%20Corporation%20in%201917%20to%20build%2019th-century-style%20wooden%20ships%20with%20steam-driven%20engines%20which%20could%20be%20produced%20at%20older%20shipyards.%20Most%20modern%20shipyards%20were%20already%20at%20capacity%20building%2020th%20century%20steel%20ships%20with%20internal%20combustion%20engines%2C%20the%20museum%20said.%20There%20were%20also%20metal%20shortages%20during%20the%20war%2C%20hence%20the%20use%20of%20timber.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20the%20war%20ended%20in%201918%2C%20the%20outdated%20wooden%20ships%2C%20which%20were%20around%20280%20feet%20long%2C%20became%20virtually%20obsolete%20overnight%2C%20and%20the%20US%20government%20struggled%20to%20sell%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20reason%20that%20you%20find%20these%20in%20the%20Neches%C2%A0is%20because%20when%20the%20war%20ended%2C%20the%20ships%20sort%20of%20lost%20their%20purpose%2C%26quot%3B%20Amy%20Borgens%2C%20the%20state%20marine%20archaeologist%20with%20the%20Texas%20Historical%20Commission%2C%20told%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.texasstandard.org%2Fstories%2Fneches-river-shipwreck-evadale-east-texas%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETexas%20Standard%3C%2Fa%3E%20public%20radio%20show.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20it%20was%20really%20difficult%20for%20the%20government%20to%20find%20buyers%20for%20wooden-hulled%20ships%20at%20that%20time.%20And%20so%20these%20vessels%2C%20many%20of%20which%20were%20constructed%20at%20a%20cost%20of%20%24250%2C000%20each%2C%20some%20of%20these%20were%20sold%20for%20just%20%241%2C000%2C%20just%20for%20the%20salvage%20of%20wood%20and%20iron.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20vessels%2C%20which%20were%20built%20in%20Beaumont%2C%20Texas%2C%20were%20eventually%20abandoned%20in%20the%20rivers%2C%20where%20the%20government%20would%20%26quot%3Blet%20salvagers%20get%20what%20they%20could%20from%20the%20iron%20and%20timber%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Ice%20House%20Museum%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22580%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Texas%20Historical%20Commission%20sonar%20data%20from%202019%20showing%20the%20submerged%20hulls%20of%20two%20of%20the%20abandoned%20World%20War%20I%20vessels%20in%20the%20Neches%20River.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64eea69e26dda200194d7f97%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22552%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETexas%20Historical%20Commission%20sonar%20data%20from%202019%20showing%20the%20submerged%20hulls%20of%20two%20of%20the%20abandoned%20World%20War%20I%20vessels%20in%20the%20Neches%20River.%3Cp%3ETexas%20Historical%20Commission%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EToday%20there%20are%20around%2020%20of%20the%20ships%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20Neches%2C%20and%20another%2015%20in%20the%20Sabine%2C%20many%20of%20which%20have%20been%20previously%20known%20to%20the%20Texas%20Historical%20Commission%2C%20Borgens%20told%20the%20Texas%20Standard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FTexasHistoricalCommission%2Fposts%2Fpfbid0b6Zz7xTYBCT39p8QFQBub4bSgYRt8ggdz44jZJNEpKLudDgtwQoyr5zRN2zMLTGQl%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETexas%20Historical%20Commission%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20on%20Facebook%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20summer%20heatwave%20and%20low%20rainfall%26quot%3B%20revealed%20the%20hidden%20shipwreck.%20The%20area%20of%20Texas%20where%20the%20ship%20was%20found%20is%20under%20extreme%20drought%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdroughtmonitor.unl.edu%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20Drought%20Monitor%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESusan%20Kilcrease%20from%20the%20Ice%20House%20Museum%20told%20Insider%20they%20believe%20the%20remnants%20Milner%20found%20and%20took%20photos%20of%20actually%20belonged%20to%20five%20ships.%20The%20museum%20said%20a%20newspaper%20article%20from%201924%20reported%20that%20six%20ships%20had%20caught%20fire%20in%20the%20Neches%20River%20north%20of%20Beaumont%20and%20burned%20down%20to%20the%20waterline.%20Kilcrease%20said%20they%20believe%20the%20recent%20discovery%20may%20be%20those%20ships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBorgens%20told%20the%20Texas%20Standard%20the%20best%20way%20to%20preserve%20the%20ships%20is%20to%20leave%20them%20be%2C%20emphasizing%20that%20the%20public%20should%20not%20try%20to%20access%20the%20shipwreck%20sites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsunken-world-war-1-wooden-ship-texas-river-jet-ski-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693362472000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64eea4ca26dda200194d7ef5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsunken-world-war-1-wooden-ship-texas-river-jet-ski-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20wreckage%20belonged%20to%20a%20wooden%20ship%20built%20in%20World%20War%201%20tha