.com%2Fgeorgia-trump-indictment-unsealed-read-full-text-charges-2023-8%5C%22%3Ea%20sprawling%20RICO%20indictment%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20accuses%20the%20group%20of%20participating%20in%20a%20racketeering%20enterprise%20that%20illegally%20pressured%20public%20officials%20to%20toss%20out%20now-President%20Joe%20Biden's%20Georgia%20victory%20during%20the%202020%20election%20and%20keep%20Trump%20in%20power%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeadows%2C%20Clark%2C%20and%20several%20other%20defendants%20have%20asked%20to%20have%20their%20cases%20removed%20to%20federal%20court.%20If%20Meadows%20is%20successful%2C%20it%20could%20pave%20the%20way%20for%20Trump%20to%20maneuver%20his%20way%20into%20federal%20court%20%E2%80%94%20where%20he%20may%20get%20a%20more%20favorable%20jury%20and%20could%20get%20less%20scrutiny%20from%20the%20cameras%20as%20he%20runs%20in%20the%202024%20presidential%20race.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20powerfully%20significant%20procedure%20because%20the%20move%20to%20federal%20court%20for%20at%20least%20three%20of%20the%20defendants%20will%20throw%20a%20big%20harpoon%20into%20the%20sea%20of%20charges%20brought%20by%20the%20state%2C%26quot%3B%20Ronald%20Carlson%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Georgia%20School%20of%20Law%2C%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIf%20lightning%20strikes%20and%20Meadows%20wins%2C%20it'll%20assist%20his%20case%20in%20a%20compelling%20way.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhy%20is%20Meadows%20%E2%80%94%20and%20potentially%20Trump%20%E2%80%94%20so%20desperate%20to%20have%20a%20trial%20in%20federal%20court%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20lawyers%20may%20believe%20that%20a%20federal%20judge%20might%20be%20more%20willing%20than%20a%20state%20judge%20to%20consider%20legal%20arguments%20that%20would%20make%20him%20immune%20from%20the%20criminal%20charges%2C%20according%20to%20Mai%20Ratakonda%2C%20a%20senior%20counsel%20at%20States%20United%20Democracy%20Center.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20federal%20court%20judge%20might%20be%20more%20sympathetic%20to%20some%20of%20their%20federal%20constitutional%20defenses%20that%20they%20might%20want%20to%20raise%2C%26quot%3B%20Ratakonda%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BSo%20if%20they%20are%20planning%20to%20raise%20defenses%20involving%2C%20for%20example%2C%20executive%20immunity%2C%20they%20might%20be%20thinking%20that%20a%20federal%20judge%20might%20be%20more%20amenable%20to%20hearing%20them%20out%20on%20those.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-meadows-asks-dismiss-georgia-rico-charges-doing-job-2023-8%5C%22%3EMeadows%20is%20the%20first%20defendant%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20have%20a%20hearing%20over%20whether%20his%20case%20should%20be%20removed%20to%20federal%20court.%20If%20the%20case%20is%20moved%2C%20a%20federal%20judge%20would%20oversee%20the%20criminal%20case%20in%20federal%20court%20instead%20of%20state%20court%2C%20but%20the%20charges%20would%20stay%20the%20same%20and%20the%20district%20attorney's%20office%20would%20still%20prosecute%20the%20case.%20Both%20Trump%20and%20Meadows%20have%20denied%20wrongdoing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20District%20Judge%20Steve%20C.%20Jones%2C%20the%20Obama-appointed%20judge%20who%20was%20randomly%20assigned%20to%20the%20case%2C%20scheduled%20a%20removal%20hearing%20for%20Clark%20on%20September%2018.%20He%20set%20another%20hearing%20on%20September%2020%20for%20David%20Shafer%20and%20Cathleen%20Latham%2C%20two%20fake%20electors%20also%20under%20indictment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20Monday%20hearing%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ajc.com%2Fpolitics%2Fbreaking-meadows-defends-actions-as-he-testifies-in-federal-court%2FYG3IFQBGGJA5BGAP5FNO74CIMI%2F%5C%22%3EMeadows%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20all%20of%20his%20actions%20were%20within%20the%20scope%20of%20his%20role%20as%20Trump's%20chief%20of%20staff.%20In%20court%20filings%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-meadows-asks-dismiss-georgia-rico-charges-doing-job-2023-8%5C%22%3Ehis%20lawyers%20have%20argued%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he's%20shielded%20by%20the%20Supremacy%20Clause%20of%20the%20US%20Constitution%2C%20which%20protects%20federal%20employees%20against%20interference%20from%20state%20officials.%20Meadows's%20conduct%2C%20they%20argued%2C%20was%20within%20%26quot%3Bhis%20official%20duties%20and%20the%20federal%20policy%20underlying%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20order%20for%20the%20court%20to%20accept%20this%20case%20as%20a%20federal%20case%2C%20the%20defendants%20have%20to%20show%20that%20they%20were%20acting%20within%20their%20capacity%20as%20federal%20officers%20when%20they%20took%20the%20actions%20that%20underlie%20the%20indictment%2C%26quot%3B%20Ratakonda%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrump%20may%20raise%20some%20of%20the%20same%20legal%20arguments%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20other%20benefits%20to%20removal.%20While%20Georgia's%20state%20courts%20are%20famed%20for%20their%20public%20access%2C%20often%20allowing%20live%20video%20cameras%20into%20courtrooms%2C%20federal%20courts%20are%20not.%20Any%20trial%20is%20sure%20to%20be%20covered%20closely%20by%20the%20media%2C%20but%20having%20it%20in%20a%20federal%20courtroom%20might%20minimize%20unsavory%20public%20images%20as%20Trump%20continues%20to%20run%20for%20the%202024%20Republican%20presidential%20nomination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20state%20court%20proceeding%20would%20also%20take%20in%20jurors%20from%20Fulton%20County%2C%20which%20voted%20overwhelmingly%20for%20Biden%20in%202020.%20A%20federal%20court%20trial%20would%20have%20a%20much%20wider%20jury%20pool%2C%20including%20from%20counties%20that%20voted%20for%20Trump%20in%20the%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20Meadows%20successfully%20shows%20he%20was%20acting%20within%20his%20duties%20as%20a%20federal%20official%20and%20gets%20his%20case%20removed%20to%20federal%20court%2C%20it%20doesn't%20mean%20Jones%20will%20automatically%20accept%20his%20arguments%20that%20he%20was%20just%20doing%20his%20job.%20The%20legal%20standards%20for%20removal%20and%20executive%20immunity%20overlap%2C%20but%20differ%20in%20important%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225144%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Donald%20Trump%2C%20Mark%20Meadows%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61f989d64faa730018ff4baa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223858%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMark%20Meadows%20and%20Donald%20Trump%20at%20the%20White%20House.%3Cp%3ESarah%20Silbiger%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20indictment%20notes%20that%20Meadows%20spoke%20to%20Georgia%20officials%20and%20traveled%20to%20the%20state%20in%20order%20to%20observe%20the%20electoral%20process.%20But%20states%20%E2%80%94%20not%20the%20federal%20government%20%E2%80%94%20historically%20oversee%20the%20voting%20process%2C%20Norm%20Eisen%2C%20a%20political%20ethics%20lawyer%2C%20told%20Insider.%20Prosecutors%20argue%20he%20took%20those%20actions%20on%20behalf%20of%20Trump's%20political%20goals%2C%20not%20as%20part%20of%20his%20chief-of-staff%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20and%20his%20legal%20team%20are%20likely%20paying%20close%20attention%20to%20Meadows's%20removal%20fight.%20Jones%20hasn't%20yet%20made%20a%20decision%2C%20and%20on%20Tuesday%20asked%20Meadows%20and%20prosecutors%20to%20file%20more%20legal%20briefings%20on%20the%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Trump%20faces%20far%20more%20risk%20than%20Meadows%20in%20the%20case%20%E2%80%94%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-criminal-cases-ranked-how-much-legal-trouble-2023-8%5C%22%3Earguably%20more%20risk%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20he%20does%20in%20any%20of%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-key-cases-civil-criminal-investigations-lawsuits-updates-2022-7%5C%22%3Ethree%20other%20indictments%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20brought%20two%20charges%20against%20Meadows%2C%20accusing%20him%20of%20racketeering%20and%20soliciting%20Geor